fields.title: Our Stores
fields.body:
Introducing Farm Feeds: Nourishing Agriculture, Enriching Lives

Welcome to Farm Feeds, your trusted partner in providing premium nutrition for a thriving agricultural community. At Farm Feeds, we understand the importance of wholesome and balanced diets for your livestock and pets, and we are committed to delivering top-quality feed products that cater to the unique nutritional needs of cattle, chickens, pigs, and dogs.

Our Commitment to Quality:
At Farm Feeds, quality is at the heart of everything we do. We source the finest ingredients to create nutritionally rich feeds that promote the health, productivity, and well-being of your animals. Our team of experts ensures that each product undergoes rigorous testing and adheres to the highest industry standards, guaranteeing optimal results for your farm animals and pets.

Comprehensive Range of Products:
Farm Feeds proudly offers a diverse range of feed products tailored to meet the specific requirements of different livestock and pets. Whether you're raising a herd of cattle, a flock of chickens, a sounder of pigs, or caring for your loyal canine companion, our extensive product line has you covered. From growth and performance feeds to special formulations for specific breeds, we have the right nutrition for every stage of life.

Cattle Nutrition:
Our cattle feed is formulated to support the nutritional needs of dairy and beef cattle. Packed with essential vitamins, minerals, and protein, our feeds contribute to optimal milk production, muscle development, and overall health.

Chicken Feed Solutions:
Farm Feeds offers a selection of poultry feeds designed to enhance egg production, support healthy feathering, and boost the immune system of your chickens. Our feeds are a key ingredient in fostering robust and productive flocks.

Pig Nutrition Excellence:
For pig farmers, our pig feeds provide the ideal balance of nutrients to promote efficient growth, reproductive health, and strong immune systems in your swine population.

Tailored Dog Nutrition:
Recognizing that dogs are an integral part of the farm family, we have crafted specialized dog feeds to keep your canine companions energetic, healthy, and ready for the challenges of farm life.

Customer-Centric Approach:
At Farm Feeds, we prioritize the satisfaction of our customers. Our knowledgeable staff is always ready to provide guidance and support, ensuring that you make informed decisions about the nutrition of your animals. We value your trust and are dedicated to building lasting relationships with our farming community.

Sustainable Farming Practices:
Farm Feeds is committed to sustainability and environmentally friendly practices. We strive to minimize our ecological footprint by sourcing ingredients responsibly and implementing eco-conscious manufacturing processes.

Choose Farm Feeds for superior nutrition, exceptional service, and a commitment to the well-being of your farm animals. Join us in nourishing agriculture and enriching lives through the power of premium feed solutions. Visit our store today and experience the Farm Feeds difference!

fields.title: Trust in Excellence – A Journey with Our Market
fields.body:
In the heart of our commitment lies a story of unwavering trust, a journey that transcends mere transactions to foster a community built on excellence and reliability. Our market stands as a beacon of trust, a testament to the values that anchor our every endeavor.

At the core of our ethos is the unwavering dedication to providing our customers with products of unparalleled quality. From the moment our customers step into our market, they embark on a journey marked by the assurance of superior offerings and a commitment to their satisfaction.

Quality that Speaks Volumes

Our market prides itself on curating a selection that speaks volumes about the meticulous attention we dedicate to quality. Every product on our shelves undergoes rigorous scrutiny, ensuring that only the finest, freshest, and most ethically sourced items find their way to our customers.

From the freshest produce to the most exquisite handcrafted goods, our market endeavors to exceed expectations. We believe that quality isn't just a feature; it's an experience that resonates with every purchase, creating a lasting impression that becomes synonymous with trust.

A Community of Trust

Trust isn't just a transaction; it's the foundation of a thriving community. Our market has cultivated an environment where every interaction is a promise, a promise that we are here not just as purveyors of goods but as partners in our customers' journey.

Our knowledgeable and friendly staff members are more than just faces behind the counter; they are stewards of trust, ready to assist, guide, and ensure that every customer feels a sense of belonging. It's not just about selling; it's about building relationships that endure.

Transparency and Integrity

In a world where transparency and integrity often feel like rare commodities, our market stands as a paragon of both. From sourcing to pricing, we uphold the principles of honesty and openness. Our customers deserve to know the story behind their purchases, and we are proud to share it.

By choosing our market, customers are not merely buying products; they are investing in a relationship built on transparency, where every detail matters and every promise is kept. Integrity is not just a value; it's the cornerstone of our identity.

Your Journey Starts Here

As you navigate the aisles of our market, envision more than a shopping trip – see it as a voyage into trust, quality, and a commitment to excellence. Your journey with us is more than a series of transactions; it's an odyssey where your needs, preferences, and satisfaction are paramount.

fields.title: Green Energy
fields.body:
Harnessing the Power of the Sun: Farm Feeds' Commitment to Sustainable Agriculture

At Farm Feeds, we recognize the critical role agriculture plays in both feeding the world and preserving the environment. That's why we've embraced the power of green energy, with a particular focus on solar systems, to not only meet our operational needs but also contribute to a more sustainable and eco-friendly future.

Solar-Powered Operations:
Farm Feeds has invested significantly in solar energy infrastructure to power our operations. By utilizing solar panels, we tap into the abundant and renewable energy provided by the sun. This not only reduces our dependence on traditional energy sources but also significantly decreases our carbon footprint. Our solar-powered facilities ensure that we can continue providing top-quality feed products while minimizing the environmental impact of our operations.

Clean and Renewable Energy:
Solar power is one of the cleanest and most sustainable sources of energy available. By harnessing the sun's energy, we avoid the emissions associated with traditional energy production methods. This commitment to clean energy aligns with our dedication to responsible and environmentally conscious business practices.

Reducing Carbon Footprint:
Farm Feeds understands the importance of mitigating climate change and reducing greenhouse gas emissions. By relying on solar energy, we actively contribute to the reduction of our carbon footprint, fostering a more sustainable agricultural sector. Our efforts in embracing green energy are not only a step towards environmental responsibility but also a demonstration of our commitment to a healthier planet for future generations.

Energy Efficiency and Cost Savings:
In addition to the environmental benefits, our solar-powered systems enhance energy efficiency and lead to significant cost savings. By utilizing the sun's energy to generate power, we reduce our reliance on grid electricity, resulting in lower operational costs. This, in turn, allows us to maintain competitive prices for our feed products, benefiting both our customers and the environment.

Educating and Inspiring:
Farm Feeds is passionate about promoting sustainability within the farming community. We actively share our experiences with implementing solar systems, encouraging others to consider renewable energy solutions for their operations. By leading through example, we aim to inspire positive change within the agricultural industry and demonstrate that sustainable practices can be both environmentally responsible and economically viable.

As a forward-thinking organization, Farm Feeds is proud to champion the use of solar energy in agriculture, demonstrating that it is not just an investment in technology but a commitment to a greener and more sustainable future. Join us on this journey towards a more environmentally conscious agriculture sector, where the power of the sun fuels not only our operations but also our collective responsibility to the planet.

fields.name: Chick Duck Mash
fields.description:
It contains energy, proteins essential amino acids, minerals, and vitamins for the healthy growth and development of layer chicks.
It also contains Cocciodiostat for the prevention of coccidiosis during the crucial period of growing layer birds.

fields.name: Chick Starter Crumbs
fields.description:
This is a high protein feed for layer and improved kienyeji chicks for the first 3 weeks of life to provide efficient growth needed in modern commercial poultry production. Chicks are able to pick feeds more effectively in the early stages without wastage.
Due to the pelleting process, the feed has better digestibility for young chicks. The feed is fortified with Coccidiostats, enzymes, probiotics plus Vitamins and minerals to ensure good takeoff in performance of chicks.

fields.name: Growers Mash
fields.description:
Well balanced for energy, proteins, vitamins, and minerals to ensure pullets attain a minimum of 1.5 kgs live weight at the point of lay, so as to quickly reach peak production and maintain high production for a long time.
Also contains Coccidistat for the prevention of coccidiosis in the growing pullets.

fields.name: Layers Mash
fields.description: This is a complete feed for laying chickens, well balanced in energy, proteins and mineral to ensure good health and high egg production of the layers.

fields.name: Layers Extra
fields.description: This is a feed designed for improved Kienyeji laying birds to achieve over 80% laying and hatchability of over 70% for farmers hatching their own chicks. The product also gives eggs with golden yellow yolk for those targeting table egg market.It is well balanced in vitamins, minerals and amino acid content

fields.name: Broiler Starter
fields.description: This is a standard meat chicken feed for young broiler chickks from day old up to 3 weeks of age.

fields.name: Broiler Starter farm
fields.description: This is a standard meat chicken feed for young broiler chicks from day old upto 3 weeks of age. Each broiler chick consumes on average 1.2kgs during this period

fields.name: Farm Gro Starter Crumbs
fields.description: This is fed from 0-21 days. Each chick consumes 0.9 to 1kgs over this period. Well managed briler chicks should weigh 940 to 950 grams live weight by by day 21 on our starter crumbs.

fields.name: Broiler Finisher Mash
fields.description:
This is a well balanced to ensure a high yield of quality meat with very low visceral fat. Each broiler bird consumes 2.8 to 3 kgs of this feed up to slaughter time.
 At slaughter time, which is 6 weeks, the bird should weigh 1.8kgs on average.

fields.name: Broiler Finisher Farm
fields.description: Broiler finisher farm is well balanced to ensure high yield of quality meat with very low visceral fat. Each broiler  bird consumes 2.8kgs to 2kgs of this product up to slaughter time. The bird should be approximately 1.8kgs at slaughter time.

fields.name: Farm Gro Finisher Pellets
fields.description: This is a feed from day 21 to slaughter (33-34) days. Each broiler chick consumes 2.2 to 2.3 kgs of feeds for this period. Expected slaughter weight on our pellets is 1.8 to 1.9 kg bird live weight.

fields.name: Kienyeji Mash
fields.description: Designed especially for local chicken and is properly balanced to meet nutritional requirements of local birds for improved productivity and growth. Ingredients include: Maize, Maize germ, Wheat pollard and Bran, Soya meal, Sunflower cake, Omena fish meal, Vitamins, minerals and Toxin Binders.

fields.name: Kienyeji Layers Extra
fields.description: This is a feed designed for improved kienyeji laying birds to achieve over 80% laying and good hatchability of over 70% for farmers hatching their own chicks. The product also gives eggs with golden yolks for those targeting table egg market. Well balanced with vitamins, amino acids and minerals

fields.name: Kienyeji Growers Mash
fields.description: Designed for local chicken and balanced to meet nutritional requirements. Ingredients include Maize, maize germ, wheat pollard, Bran, 'Omena' fish meal, vitamins, and sun flower cake.

fields.name: Sow and weaner
fields.description:
This is a new innovation in our pigs feed range. It is designed for lactating sows and gilts to achieve good milk production and healthy body condition during and after suckling.
This ensures high fertility and productivity of sows. The feed is formulated with mordern technology to achieve good nutrient balance for its purpose. Average feed intake per suckling sow is 5kgs

fields.name: Pig grower meal
fields.description: This is a well balanced meal full of nutrients composition to ensure healthy growth of younger growing pigs. It is fed from 13-21 weeks

fields.name: Dairy Meal standard
fields.description:
This is a dairy concentrate formulated for dairy cows that have a production of 10-20 liters of milk per day.
For cows on low quality of forage, give 1 kg for every 1.5 liters of milk above 7kg produced per cow per day. For cows that are on good quality forage give 1 kg for every 1.5 litres above 10 kgs produced per cow per day.

fields.name: Dairy cubes
fields.description:
This is a pelleted Dairy Concentrate with specifications as for Dairy Standard Meal. Pelleting makes this product less wasteful. There is more saliva during chewing ensuring more rumen buffering and digestibility.
Product is popular in dry areas, as animals spend less time feeding, allowing more rest time, hence more milk production.
Product is highly palatable due to the cooking process.

fields.name: Range cubes
fields.description:
This is a pelletted maintenance diet to supplement natural forage during dry periods. The pellet form ensures no wastage during feeding and animals are able to feed within a short time and effectively chew to enhance digestibility.
It is suitable for both large and small ruminants.

fields.name: BETA FARM YIELD
fields.description: This is the most popular brand in the market for cows producing 20-25 liters daily. On average, give 1kg of Beta for every 2 liters of milk produced above 10 kg per cow daily.

fields.name: Skipa Dog meal
fields.description:
This is a high quality aflatoxin-free, uncooked, dry meal for all ages and breeds of dogs.
It contains high specifications of energy and proteins, sterelized meat and bone meal for all ages and breeds of dogs.
Contains high levels of calcium and phosphorus for the development of strong bones, and robust body health. Contains toxin binders to ensure it is free of mycotoxins
